$lang['You can use hexadecimal to convert between decimal and binary values. For example, converting 10011011001010 into hexadecimal would result in 0x4F. This means that the value 4F represents the binary number 100110110010110.'] = 'Gatii kurnyee fi baayinarii gidduutti jijjiiruuf heksaadesimaalii fayyadamuu dandeessa. Fakkeenyaaf, 10011011001010 gara heksaadesimaaliitti jijjiiruun 0x4F argamsiisa. Kana jechuun gatii 4F lakkoofsa baayinarii 100110110010110 bakka bu&#39;a.';
$lang['In mathematics and computer science, hexadecimal (also base 16, or hex) is a positional numeral system with a radix, or base, of 16. It uses sixteen distinct symbols, most often the symbols 0–9 to represent values zero to nine, and A, B, C, D, E, F (or alternatively a–f) to represent values ten to fifteen. For example, the hexadecimal number 2AF3 is equal, in decimal, to (2 × 163) + (10 × 162) + (15 × 161) + (3 × 160) , or 10,995.'] = 'Herregaa fi saayinsii kompiitaraa keessatti, heksaadesimaaliin (akkasumas bu’uura 16, ykn heeks) sirna lakkoofsa iddoo kan raadiksii, ykn bu’uura, 16. Mallattoolee adda addaa kudha jaha fayyadama, yeroo baay’ee mallattoolee 0–9 gatiiwwan zeeroo hanga sagal bakka bu’uuf, . fi A, B, C, D, E, F (ykn filannoo biraa a–f) gatiiwwan kudhan hanga kudha shan bakka bu’uuf. Fakkeenyaaf, lakkoofsi heksaadesimaalii 2AF3, kurnyeedhaan, (2 × 163) + (10 × 162) + (15 × 161) + (3 × 160) , ykn 10,995 wajjin walqixa.';
$lang['Each hexadecimal digit represents four binary digits (bits) (also called a "nibble"), and the primary use of hexadecimal notation is as a human-friendly representation of binary coded values in computing and digital electronics. For example, byte values can range from 0 to 255 (decimal) but may be more conveniently represented as two hexadecimal digits in the range 00 through FF. Hexadecimal is also commonly used to represent computer memory addresses.'] = 'Tokkoon tokkoon dijiitii heksaadesimaalii dijiitota baayinarii (bit) afur bakka bu&#39;a (&quot;nibble&quot; jedhamuunis ni waamama), fi itti fayyadamni jalqabaa mallattoo heksaadesimaalii akka bakka bu&#39;iinsa namaaf mijatu gatiiwwan koodii baayinarii shallaggii fi elektirooniksii dijiitaalaa keessatti. Fakkeenyaaf, gatiiwwan baayitii 0 hanga 255 (kurnyee) ta&#39;uu danda&#39;u garuu akka dijiitota heksaadesimaal lamaatti hanga 00 hanga FF keessatti haala mijataa ta&#39;een bakka bu&#39;uu danda&#39;u. Heksaadesimaaliin teessoo yaadannoo kompiitaraa bakka bu’uufis yeroo baay’ee fayyadama.';
$lang['Hex is an abbreviation of Hexadecimal, which is based on a base -16 structure and is used for simplifying how instructions to computers are represented. This 16 symbols number system was developed as a means of inhibiting an 8-bit binary number, so data can be encoded into computers effortlessly. It can be imprinted and typed using two different hex digits with each hex digit demonstrating a nibble or perhaps a 4-bits format.'] = 'Hex gabaabduu Heksadesimaal yoo ta’u, kunis caasaa bu’uuraa -16 irratti kan hundaa’ee fi akkaataa qajeelfamni gara kompitaraatti kennamu salphisuuf kan gargaarudha. Sirni lakkoofsa mallattoo 16 kun akka mala lakkoofsa baayinarii 8-bit dhorkuuf kan qophaa’e waan ta’eef, daataa dadhabbii malee gara kompitaraatti koodii ta’uu danda’a. Dijiitota heksii adda addaa lama fayyadamuun maxxanfamuu fi barreessuu ni danda&#39;ama tokkoon tokkoon dijiitii heksaasii nibble ykn tarii bifa 4-bit agarsiisa.';
$lang['This number system uses 16 symbols that are represented in a range from 0-9 or A-F. The 0–9 represent numbers up to nine whereas A-F is represented by the numeric 10–15. As compared to the other three types of number systems, the hexadecimal numeral system is considered to be the most effective one.'] = 'Sirni lakkoofsaa kun mallattoolee 16 kan 0-9 ykn AF gidduutti bakka bu&#39;an fayyadama. 0–9n lakkoofsota hanga sagaliitti kan bakka bu’an yoo ta’u AF ammoo lakkoofsa 10–15n bakka bu’a. Sirna lakkoofsaa gosoota sadan kanneen biroo wajjin wal bira qabamee yoo ilaalamu sirni lakkoofsaa heksaadesimaalii isa hunda caalaa bu’a qabeessa ta’ee fudhatama.';
